@node 1
 What's New in Version 2

 * Linking - create links between items (for example, an address to an
   appointment).

 * Diary Event scroll arrows - when a diary event has more events than
   can be displayed, two arrows appear to the right of the day view so
   that you can scroll the events up and down.

 *** @{" See Fig 1 The Organiser 2 New Display " system "ps OrgDocs:fig1"} ***

 * Diary Themes - themed events now appear in grey to be easily
   distinguishable from normal events, and no longer appear in the
   Calendar section.

 * Diary Themes - change themes at any time using the Open command.

 * Addresses - on page marking (by clicking the checkbox on the Address
   view).

 * Addresses - improved DigiSense now includes Auto Capitalisation to
   correctly capitalise names, addresses and postcodes.

 * Addresses - new salutation field (for Mr, Mrs, Dr and so on).

 * Supplements - a new command, "Rescan Disk" (on the Supplements sub-
   menu, Locate menu) which re-scans the Supplements drawer. This allows
   you to freely add or remove Supplements without quitting Organiser.

 * Supplements - new navigation buttons on the ribbon bar.

 * Settings - new settings (“General Settings” requester) for greater
   flexibility.

 * Speed improvements.

 * Erase Items requester includes option for Diary Theme events.

 Page 1

@endnode
@node 2
 Linking

 If you store items which are related (an address and a diary appointment
for example), it makes sense to link them.

 When items are linked, a small paperclip icon appears to the right of
each item.

 Click the paperclip to reveal a pop-up menu listing all of the items that
are linked to it. Choose any item from the list and Organiser will
automatically turn to the related page.

 *** @{" See Fig 2 Pop-up List Showing Linked Items " system "ps OrgDocs:fig2"} ***

 To remove a link, choose Remove from the pop-up list, and select the link
you want to remove from the requester.

@endnode
@node 3
 Examples

 You have a meeting with Bill Smith from Wimley Electronics at 9.00am:

 1. Create an address for Bill Smith.

 2. With this item selected choose "Linked Item - Diary Event" (Create
    menu). The page turns to the Diary section and the "Diary Event
    Details" requester appears.

 3. Notice that Organiser has already placed bill Smith`s name into the
    Title gadget for you.

 Your parent`s Wedding Anniversary:

 1. Create a yearly repeating "Diary Event" for your parents` wedding
    anniversary.

 2. With this item selected, choose "Linked Item-Task" (Create menu).
    The page turns to the Task section and the "Task Details" requester
    appears.

 Page 2

 3. Type Buy a Wedding Anniversary present for Mum and Dad into the
    Title gadget.

 4. Click the paperclip that appears to the right of the new task and
    choose the first item at the top of the pop-up list, "Parents
    Wedding Anniversary". this will turn you back to the diary event.

@endnode
@node 4
 New Menu Commands

 "Linked Item" sub-menu

 Choose "Linked Item" (Create menu) to display a sub-menu of commands.
Choosing one of these commands will create an item that is automatically
linked to the current selection.

 This command is only available if an item on the Organiser page is
`selected`. A selected item is shown by a dotted line under the first line
of text.

 When a command is chosen from the sub menu, the page is turned to the
appropriate section and an empty details requester appears. This new item
is automatically linked to the item selected when the command was chosen.

@endnode
@node 5
 "Make Link" command

 Choose "Make Link" (Create menu) to link the selected item with an
existing item in  the Organiser Diary, Task or Address sections (the
command is only available when an item is selected which is indicated by a
dotted line under the first line of text).

 When the pointer changes into a paperclip, click the item you want to
link to. To link several items, hold down the Shift key when clicking each
item.

 You can cancel at any time by pressing the Esc key.

@endnode
@node 6
 New Keyboard Shortcuts

 KEY                   Command

 Right Amiga-L         Make link
 Esc                   Exits “Make Link”
 Alt Ctrl-E            Create Linked Event
 Alt Ctrl-T            Create Linked Task
 Alt Ctrl-A            Create Linked Address
 Alt-click a Task      Marks/Unmarks item as completed
 Alt-click an Address  Marks/Unmarks item

  Navigating Through Supplements


 KEY        DOES

 Shift-,    Previous Supplement
 Shift-.    Next Supplement

 Page 3

@endnode
@node 7
 Organiser 96 Plus Pack

 The Diary Themes and Supplements contained in the 96 Plus Pack are
suitable for any version of Organiser, but it needs to be installed before
you can use it.

@endnode
@node 8
 Floppy Disk Users

 You need two blank floppy disks onto which the installer will copy the
new Diary Themes and Supplements. The installer will name these two disks
96PlusPack-1 and 96PlusPack-2.

 Switch on your Amiga and insert your Organiser disk into the internal
disk drive. When the Workbench screen appears, insert the
96PlusPackInstall disk, double-click its disk icon, and then double-click
the Install 96 Plus Pack icon.

 To use the Diary themes with Organiser, first start Organiser. Chose Open
command (Project menu) and insert the 96PlusPack-1 disk into the disk
drive. Select the 96 Plus Pack Themes drawer from the list and a list of
available themes will appear. Select a theme from the list and click Open
(Organiser 2 users can change themes at any time by repeating this
procedure).

 To add a Supplement, drag the required icon(s) from one of the Plus Pack
disks to the Supplements drawer on your Organiser program disk (drag only
individual icons, not the drawers). With Organiser 2, you just choose
Supplements - "Rescan Disk" (Locate menu) to update the Supplements menu.
Organiser 1 or 1.1 users will need to quit Organiser and restart for the
new Supplements to appear.

@endnode
@node 9
 Hard Disk Users

 You need about 3MB of hard disk space.

 Switch on your Amiga and insert when the Workbench screen appears, insert
the 96PlusPackInstall disk, double-click its disk icon, and then double-
click the Install 96 Plus Pack icon.

 The installer will install two new drawers at the location of Organiser,
96 Plus Pack Themes and 96 Plus Pack Supplements.

 To use the Diary themes with Organiser, first start Organiser. Chose Open
command (Project menu) and select the 96 Plus Pack Themes drawer. Select a
theme from the list and click Open (Organiser 2 users can change themes at
any time by repeating this procedure).

 To add a Supplement, drag the required icon(s) from one of the Plus Pack
disks to the Supplements drawer on your Organiser program disk (drag only
individual icons, not the drawers). With Organiser 2, you just choose
Supplements - "Rescan Disk" (Locate menu) to update the Supplements menu.
Organiser 1 or 1.1 users will need to quit Organiser and restart for the
new Supplements to appear.

 Page 4

@endnode
